frameDefinitions: This frame concerns entities conventionally being referred to by particular names.
A Speaker uses a particular linguistic form, a Name to refer to an Entity.
The words in this frame describe entities that occur in some temporally-ordered sequence.
A Term is the linguistic sign conventionally used by a Speaker to refer to a type of Entity.
A Phenomenon is related to some cognitive action, the Endeavor, of a Cognizer.
A salient Subevent has a Pattern of recurrence within a larger Process.
frameExamples: They corresponded frequently and at length, exchanging intimate letters in which he <t>addressed</t> her as Windflower.
Describe in detail the <t>sequence</t> of steps taken during an emergency.
Perianth is a collective <t>term</t> for the outer whorls of the flower, which protect the reproductive parts during development.
This book is very <t>relevant</t> to my essay.
Tony's fingers tapped <t>rhythmically</t> on the keyboard
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Name</fen> identifies the linguistic expression used to refer to Entities.
The <fen>Entity</fen> is the person the speaker intends to refer to by using a particular name.
The person who uses the <fen>Name</fen>  to refer to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The entity that is designated by the <fen>Speaker</fen> with the <fen>Name</fen> used.
The linguistic form used by the <fen>Speaker</fen> to refer to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The point of time or interval when the <fen>Speaker</fen> uses the <fen>Name</fen>.
This entity occurs in some sequence with <fen>Entity_2</fen>.
This entity occurs in some sequence with respect to <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
<fen>Entities</fen> that occur in some temporal order.
A characterization of the sequence in which the entities occur.
The linguistic sign that is used for referring to a type of <fen>Entity</fen>.
The type of <fen>Entity</fen> that is conventionally referred to by a <fen>Term</fen>.
Something that is profiled in the mind of the <fen>Cognizer</fen> as being related to mental <fen>Endeavor</fen>s.
A cognitive action (eg discussion, decision) performed by the <fen>Cognizer</fen> to which the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is connected in some way.
A participant in the mental <fen>Endeavor</fen> to which the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is related. This frame element is often null-instantiated and may be inferred from the <fen>Endeavor</fen>.
The larger event that is characterized by the recurring Subevents.
The salient, punctual event that is construed as part of a <fen>Process</fen>.
The <fen>Pattern</fen> that can be detected in the recurrence of  the <fen>Subevent</fen>s of the <fen>Process</fen> .
listRoleExamples: <fex>The Lord, who was charmed by her beauty,</fex> addressed her as 'than kaadhali!' (My darling) and hence the name.
And that's the reason why we called <fex>him</fex> 'Tom' when his real name was actually John.
A male voice answered the call, and Jones addressed the man as <fex>'Johnny.'</fex>
No one had <fex>ever</fex> called her 'my lady'.
The study consisted of a <fex>chronologically varied</fex> SERIES of grotesque heads.
The French term for this is <fex>rime pauvre or rime faible</fex>.
Jews are still waiting for the 'annointed one' to come; their word <fex>for this</fex> is Messiah.
The rhythm <fex>of the rain falling on the roof</fex> kept me awake
The music had a driving rhythm
